The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing an image from compressive measurements, which is a common topic in the field of information theory (cs.IT) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a multi-resolution grid is also relevant to the fields of multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the comparison between the multi-resolution and single-resolution approaches involves a performance evaluation, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
